The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on October 10, 2013. The memorandum addresses the provision of U.S. drug interdiction assistance to the government of Brazil. The President certifies that the interdiction of aircraft suspected of being involved in illicit drug trafficking in Brazil's airspace is necessary due to the significant threat it poses to the country's national security. The memorandum also states that Brazil has appropriate procedures in place to protect against innocent loss of life during such interdiction efforts. The Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish this determination in the Federal Register and notify Congress.